summary: No known completeness proof method can handle the codebase's novel semantics (parametric time D, box quantifying over ALL histories) without architectural changes. The universal history quantification represents second-order logic, making standard completeness techniques inapplicable.

artifacts.summary: Evaluates Option E (alternative completeness methods): Henkin-style, ultraproduct, direct canonical, FOL translation, and algebraic approaches all fail due to second-order history quantification
